<inglise> Council Directive 93/96/EEC of 29 October 1993 on the right of residence for students </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU DIREKTIIV 93/96/EM&Uuml; &otilde;pilaste &otilde;iguse kohta teises liikmesriigis elada 29. oktoober 1993 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community, and in particular the second paragraph of Article 7 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artikli 7 teist l&otilde;iku, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission (1), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, (1) </eesti>
<inglise> In cooperation with the European Parliament (2), </inglise>
<eesti> koost&ouml;&ouml;s Euroopa Parlamendiga, (2) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the Economic and Social Committee (3), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse majandus- ja sotsiaalkomitee arvamust (3) </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Article 3 (c) of the Treaty provides that the activities of the Community shall include, as provided in the Treaty, the abolition, as between Member States, of obstacles to freedom of movement for persons; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: asutamislepingu artikli 3 punktis c n&auml;hakse ette, et &uuml;henduse tegevuse hulka kuulub vastavalt asutamislepingule isikute vaba liikumise takistuste k&otilde;rvaldamine liikmesriikide vahel; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Article 8a of the Treaty provides that the internal market must be established by 31 December 1992; whereas the internal market comprises an area without internal frontiers in which the free movement of goods, persons, services and capital is ensured in accordance with the provisions of the Treaty; </inglise>
<eesti> asutamislepingu artikliga 8a n&auml;hakse ette siseturu rajamine 31. detsembriks 1992; siseturg h&otilde;lmab sisepiirideta ala, mille ulatuses tagatakse kaupade, isikute, teenuste ja kapitali vaba liikumine vastavalt asutamislepingu s&auml;tetele; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, as the Court of Justice has held, Articles 128 and 7 of the Treaty prohibit any discrimination between nationals of the Member States as regards access to vocational training in the Community; whereas access by a national of one Member State to vocational training in another Member State implies, for that national, a right of residence in that other Member State; </inglise>
<eesti> vastavalt Euroopa Kohtu otsusele ei tohi asutamislepingu artiklite 128 ja 7 kohaselt diskrimineerida liikmesriikide kodanikke seoses kutse&otilde;ppe k&auml;ttesaadavusega &uuml;henduses; kui kutse&otilde;pe on &uuml;he liikmesriigi kodanikule k&auml;ttesaadav teises liikmesriigis, kaasneb sellega &otilde;igus teises liikmesriigis elada; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, accordingly, in order to guarantee access to vocational training, the conditions likely to facilitate the effective exercise of that right of residence should be laid down; </inglise>
<eesti> sellele vastavalt tuleks kutse&otilde;ppe k&auml;ttesaadavuse tagamiseks s&auml;testada tingimused, mis soodustaksid teises liikmesriigis elamise &otilde;iguse t&otilde;husat teostamist; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the right of residence for students forms part of a set of related measures designed to promote vocational training; </inglise>
<eesti> &otilde;pilaste teises liikmesriigis elamise &otilde;igus on osa omavahel seotud meetmete kogumist, mille eesm&auml;rk on kutse&otilde;pet edendada; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas beneficiaries of the right of residence must not become an unreasonable burden on the public finances of the host Member State; </inglise>
<eesti> teises liikmesriigis elamise &otilde;iguse kasutajad ei tohi p&otilde;hjendamatult koormata vastuv&otilde;tva liikmesriigi eelarvet; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in the present state of Community law, as established by the case law of the Court of Justice, assistance granted to students, does not fall within the scope of the Treaty within the meaning of Article 7 thereof; </inglise>
<eesti> &uuml;henduse &otilde;iguse praeguse olukorraga, mis on kujunenud Euroopa Kohtu kohtupraktika alusel, ei kuulu &otilde;pilastele antav toetus asutamislepingu artikli 7 kohaselt asutamislepingu reguleerimisalasse; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the right of residence can only be genuinely exercised if it is also granted to the spouse and their dependent children; </inglise>
<eesti> &otilde;igust teises riigis elada saab tegelikult teostada &uuml;ksnes juhul, kui sama &otilde;igus antakse ka isiku abikaasale ning nende &uuml;lalpeetavatele lastele; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the beneficiaries of this Directive should be covered by administrative arrangements similar to those laid down in particular in Council Directive 68/360/EEC of 15 October 1968 on the abolition of restrictions on movement and residence within the Community for workers of Member States and their families (4) and Council Directive 64/221/EEC of 25 February 1964 on the coordination of special measures concerning the movement and residence of foreign nationals which are justified on grounds of public policy, public security or public health (5); </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esoleva direktiivi subjektide suhtes tuleks kohaldada samalaadset halduskorda, nagu on ette n&auml;htud eelk&otilde;ige n&otilde;ukogu 15. oktoobri 1968. aasta direktiiviga 68/360/EM&Uuml; (4) liikmesriikide t&ouml;&ouml;tajate ja nende perekondade liikumis- ja elamispiirangute kaotamise kohta &uuml;henduse piires ning n&otilde;ukogu 25. veebruari 1964. aasta direktiiviga 64/221/EM&Uuml;, (5) mis k&auml;sitleb v&auml;lisriikide kodanike liikumis- v&otilde;i elukoha&otilde;iguse suhtes kohaldatavate erimeetmete koosk&otilde;lastamist avaliku korra, julgeoleku v&otilde;i tervishoiu p&otilde;hjendusel; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas this Directive does not apply to students who enjoy the right of residence by virtue of the fact that they are or have been effectively engaged in economic activities or are members of the family of a migrant worker; </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esolevat direktiivi ei kohaldata &otilde;pilaste suhtes, kel on &otilde;igus teises riigis elada seet&otilde;ttu, et nad osalevad t&otilde;husalt majandustegevuses v&otilde;i on sisser&auml;nnanud t&ouml;&ouml;taja pereliikmed; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, by its judgment of 7 July 1992 in Case C-295/90, the Court of Justice annulled Council Directive 90/366/EEC of 28 June 1990 on the right of residence for students (1), while maintaining the effects of the annulled Directive until the entry into force of a directive adopted on the appropriate legal basis; </inglise>
<eesti> 7. juuli 1992. aasta otsusega asjas C-295/90 tunnistas Euroopa Kohus kehtetuks n&otilde;ukogu 28. juuni 1990. aasta direktiivi 90/366/EM&Uuml; (1) &otilde;pilaste &otilde;iguse kohta teises liikmesriigis elada, kuid j&auml;ttis selle direktiivi toime kehtima, kuni kohasel &otilde;iguslikul alusel v&otilde;etakse vastu uus direktiiv; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the effects of Directive 90/366/EEC should be maintained during the period up to 31 December 1993, the date by which Member States are to have adopted the laws, regulations and administrative provisions necessary to comply with this Directive, </inglise>
<eesti> direktiivi 90/366/EM&Uuml; toime peaks kehtima 31. detsembrini 1993, mil liikmesriigid peavad olema vastu v&otilde;tnud k&auml;esoleva direktiivi t&auml;itmiseks vajalikud &otilde;igus- ja haldusnormid, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS DIRECTIVE: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA DIREKTIIVI. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> In order to lay down conditions to facilitate the exercise of the right of residence and with a view to guaranteeing access to vocational training in a non-discriminatory manner for a national of a Member State who has been accepted to attend a vocational training course in another Member State, the Member States shall recognize the right of residence for any student who is a national of a Member State and who does not enjoy that right under other provisions of Community law, and for the student's spouse and their dependent children, where the student assures the relevant national authority, by means of a declaration or by such alternative means as the student may choose that are at least equivalent, that he has sufficient resources to avoid becoming a burden on the social assistance system of the host Member State during their period of residence, provided that the student is enrolled in a recognized educational establishment for the principal purpose of following a vocational training course there and that he is covered by sickness insurance in respect of all risks in the host Member State. </inglise>
<eesti> Selleks et luua teises liikmesriigis elamise &otilde;iguse kasutamist soodustavad tingimused ning tagada ilma diskrimineerimiseta kutse&otilde;ppe k&auml;ttesaadavus sellele liikmesriigi kodanikule, kes on vastu v&otilde;etud kutse&otilde;ppekursusele teises liikmesriigis, tunnustavad liikmesriigid k&otilde;ikide teise liikmesriigi kodanikest &otilde;pilaste &otilde;igust elada teises liikmesriigis, kui neil ei ole seda &otilde;igust teiste &uuml;henduse s&auml;tete kohaselt, ja &otilde;pilase abikaasa ja nende &uuml;lalpeetavate laste &otilde;igust elada teises liikmesriigis, juhul kui &otilde;pilane t&otilde;endab asjaomasele siseriiklikule asutusele avaldusega v&otilde;i omal valikul muu v&auml;hemalt v&otilde;rdv&auml;&auml;rse samalaadse dokumendiga, et tal on piisavalt vahendeid selleks, et mitte koormata vastuv&otilde;tva liikmesriigi sotsiaalabis&uuml;steemi seal elamise ajal, - k&otilde;nealune &otilde;igus elada teises liikmesriigis antakse tingimusel, et &otilde;pilane on registreerunud akrediteeritud &otilde;ppeasutuses eesm&auml;rgiga l&auml;bida seal kutse&otilde;ppekursus ning et tal on tervisekindlustus, mis katab vastuv&otilde;tvas liikmesriigis k&otilde;ik ohud. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The right of residence shall be restricted to the duration of the course of studies in question. </inglise>
<eesti> Teises liikmesriigis elamise &otilde;iguse t&auml;htaeg on piiratud k&otilde;nealuste &otilde;pingute kestusega. </eesti>
<inglise> The right of residence shall be evidenced by means of the issue of a document known as a 'residence permit for a national of a Member State of the Community', the validity of which may be limited to the duration of the course of studies or to one year where the course lasts longer; in the latter event it shall be renewable annually. </inglise>
<eesti> Teises liikmesriigis elamise &otilde;igust t&otilde;endatakse dokumendiga, mille nimi on "&uuml;henduse liikmesriigi kodanike elamisluba" ning mille kehtivusaega v&otilde;ib piirata &otilde;pingute kestusega v&otilde;i &uuml;he aastaga, kui &otilde;pingud v&auml;ltavad &uuml;le &uuml;he aasta; viimasel juhul uuendatakse luba igal aastal. </eesti>
<inglise> Where a member of the family does not hold the nationality of a Member State, he or she shall be issued with a residence document of the same validity as that issued to the national on whom he or she depends. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui pereliikmel ei ole liikmesriigi kodakondsust, antakse talle teises liikmesriigis elamise &otilde;iguse kohta sama kehtivusajaga t&otilde;end, kui teda &uuml;lal pidavale abikaasale. </eesti>
<inglise> For the purpose of issuing the residence permit or document, the Member State may require only that the applicant present a valid identity card or passport and provide proof that he or she meets the conditions laid down in Article 1. </inglise>
<eesti> Elamisloa v&otilde;i t&otilde;endi v&auml;ljaandmiseks v&otilde;ib liikmesriik &uuml;ksnes n&otilde;uda, et taotleja esitaks kehtiva isikutunnistuse v&otilde;i passi ning t&otilde;endaks, et ta vastab artiklis 1 s&auml;testatud tingimustele. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Articles 2, 3 and 9 of Directive 68/360/EEC shall apply mutatis mutandis to the beneficiaries of this Directive. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva direktiivi subjektide suhtes kohaldatakse mutatis mutandis direktiivi 68/360/EM&Uuml; artikleid 2, 3 ja 9. </eesti>
<inglise> The spouse and the dependent children of a national of a Member State entitled to the right of residence within the territory of a Member State shall be entitled to take up any employed or self-employed activity anywhere within the territory of that Member State, even if they are not nationals of a Member State. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigi kodaniku abikaasa ja &uuml;lalpeetavad lapsed, kellel on &otilde;igus liikmesriigi territooriumil elada, v&otilde;ivad selle liikmesriigi territooriumil olla t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;tjaks v&otilde;i f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust ettev&otilde;tjaks, seda ka juhul, kui nad ei ole liikmesriigi kodanikud. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall not derogate from the provisions of this Directive save on grounds of public policy, public security or public health; in that event, Articles 2 to 9 of Directive 64/221/EEC shall apply. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid v&otilde;ivad k&auml;esoleva direktiivi s&auml;tetest k&otilde;rvale kalduda &uuml;ksnes avaliku korra, julgeoleku v&otilde;i tervishoiu p&otilde;hjendusel; sellisel juhul kohaldatakse direktiivi 64/221/EM&Uuml; artikleid 2-9. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> This Directive shall not establish any entitlement to the payment of maintenance grants by the host Member State on the part of students benefiting from the right of residence. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva direktiiviga ei n&auml;hta teises liikmesriigis elamise &otilde;iguse alusel riigis viibivatele &otilde;pilastele ette mingisugust &otilde;igust saada vastuv&otilde;tvalt liikmesriigilt toimetulekutoetust. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> The right of residence shall remain for as long as beneficiaries of that right fulfil the conditions laid down in Article 1. </inglise>
<eesti> Teises liikmesriigis elamise &otilde;igus kehtib seni, kui &otilde;iguse kasutajad t&auml;idavad artiklis 1 s&auml;testatud tingimusi. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 5 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 5 </eesti>
<inglise> The Commission shall, not more than three years after the date of implementation of this Directive, and at three-yearly intervals thereafter, draw up a report on the application of this Directive and submit it to the European Parliament and the Council. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjon koostab hiljemalt kolm aastat p&auml;rast k&auml;esoleva direktiivi j&otilde;ustumist ning p&auml;rast seda kolmeaastaste vaheaegadega aruande direktiivi kohaldamise kohta ning esitab selle Euroopa Parlamendile ja n&otilde;ukogule. </eesti>
<inglise> The Commission shall pay particular attention to any difficulties to which the implementation of Article 1 might give rise in the Member States; it shall, if appropriate, submit proposals to the Council with the aim of remedying such difficulties. </inglise>
<eesti> Erit&auml;helepanu p&ouml;&ouml;rab komisjon liikmesriikides artikli 1 kohaldamisel tekkida v&otilde;ivatele probleemidele; vajaduse korral esitab ta n&otilde;ukogule ettepanekud probleemide lahendamise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 6 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 6 </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall bring into force the laws, regulations and administrative provisions necessary to comply with this Directive not later than 31 December 1993. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid j&otilde;ustavad k&auml;esoleva direktiivi j&auml;rgimiseks vajalikud &otilde;igus- ja haldusnormid hiljemalt 31. detsembril 1993. </eesti>
<inglise> They shall forthwith inform the Commission thereof. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid teatavad sellest viivitamata komisjonile. </eesti>
<inglise> For the period preceding that date, the effects of Directive 90/366/EEC shall be maintained. </inglise>
<eesti> Kuni nimetatud kuup&auml;evani kehtib direktiivi 90/366/EM&Uuml; toime. </eesti>
<inglise> When Member States adopt those measures, they shall contain a reference to this Directive or shall be accompanied by such a reference on the occasion of their official publication. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui liikmesriigid need normid vastu v&otilde;tavad, lisavad nad nendesse normidesse v&otilde;i nende normide ametliku avaldamise korral nende juurde viite k&auml;esolevale direktiivile. </eesti>
<inglise> The methods of making such references shall be laid down by the Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> Viitamise viisi n&auml;evad ette liikmesriigid. </eesti>
